HEADWORD: Hythe
<hw>Hythe</hw> <pr>(h⟦imac⟧⟦th⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A small haven.
See <er>Hithe</er>.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark></p>

<p><-- bottom of page 722. Next page is 723, starting "I" --></p>

<p><q>A dictionary containing a natural history requires too many
<qex>hands</qex>, as well as too much time, ever to be hoped for.</q>
<rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj></p>


